== Extracted Prose 1
 A collective field formalism for nonrelativistic fermions in (1+1) dimensions is presented. The quantum mechanical fermionic problem is bosonized and converted to a second quantized Schr\"odinger field theory. A formulation in terms of current and density variables gives rise to the collective field representation. Applications to the math expression hermitian matrix model and the system of one-dimensional fermions in the presence of a weak electromagnetic field are discussed. =0
